## Plan: Add Pagination to `GET /users`

**Scope: one file changed — `src/routes.ts`**

---

### What I found in the codebase

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/app.ts` | Express app setup (no changes needed) |
| `src/routes.ts` | ✏️ **Only file to modify** |
| `src/data.ts` | 15 hardcoded users in an in-memory array |
| `src/types.ts` | `User` interface (no changes needed) |
| `tests/routes.test.ts` | Vitest + Supertest tests — **already written**, must pass |

---

### The change to `src/routes.ts`

Replace the current flat-array handler:
```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json(users);  // ← returns everything
});
```

With:
```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1);
  const limit = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10);

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const start      = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data       = users.slice(start, start + limit);

  res.json({
    data,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages },
  });
});
```

---

### How each test case is satisfied

| Test | Params | Behaviour |
|------|--------|-----------|
| Default page & limit | _(none)_ | page=1, limit=10 → 10 users, totalPages=2 |
| Second page | `?page=2&limit=10` | slice(10,20) → 5 users |
| Custom limit | `?limit=5` | slice(0,5) → 5 users, totalPages=3 |
| Out-of-range | `?page=100` | slice(990,1000) → `[]`, status 200 |
| Single user | `GET /users/1` | unchanged, returns Alice |
| 404 | `GET /users/999` | unchanged, returns 404 |

